# Privacy Policy — Minimal Launcher Focus

**Last updated:** 2025

Minimal Launcher Focus ("the app") is a home screen launcher with optional focus-guard and productivity features. This policy describes how the app handles data.

## Data we use (on your device)

The app stores settings and content **only on your device**, including:

- Launcher preferences (theme, font size, home layout)
- Notes, habits, checklist, and task data
- Focus guard (delay/time limit) app list and settings
- Pinned and favourite apps

This data is **not** sent to our servers. We do not operate any backend that receives your data.

## Permissions and how they are used

The app may request these permissions. You can deny any of them; some features will then be unavailable.

| Permission | Purpose |
|------------|--------|
| **Contacts (READ_CONTACTS)** | Used only for the command box "call by name" feature (e.g. "call John") so the app can look up a contact’s number. Contact data is used only on device and is **not** sent to us or any third party. |
| **Location (fine/coarse)** | Used for weather and AQI on the home screen and for location-based news. Coordinates are sent only to the weather/AQI provider (Open-Meteo) to fetch weather; we do not store or sell location. |
| **Calendar (READ_CALENDAR)** | Used to show today’s events on the home screen. Calendar data is read only on device and is **not** sent to us. |
| **Phone (CALL_PHONE)** | Used to place calls when you use the command box or dialer shortcut. |
| **Notifications** | Optional: to show notification badges and to support "mute all except calls and messages." Notification content is processed on device only. |
| **Usage access (PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS)** | Optional: for Focus guard time limits. Used only on device to measure app usage; **not** sent to us. |
| **Other** | Internet: for news feeds and weather. Storage/install: for app list and optional uninstall. |

## Third-party services

- **Weather / AQI:** If you use the weather feature, approximate location (latitude/longitude) is sent to [Open-Meteo](https://open-meteo.com/) to retrieve weather and air quality. Their policy applies to that data.
- **News:** The app fetches public RSS feeds (e.g. BBC, The Hindu, NPR) by country. No personal data is sent to these sources; the request is for public content only.

We do not use analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs. We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties for marketing.

## Your choices

- You can revoke any permission in system Settings → Apps → Minimal Launcher Focus → Permissions.
- Disabling "Use device location" in the app’s settings stops location from being used for weather/news.
- Uninstalling the app removes all app data from the device.

## Changes

We may update this policy occasionally. The "Last updated" date at the top will be revised. Continued use of the app after changes means you accept the updated policy.

## Contact

For privacy-related questions about Minimal Launcher Focus, open an issue or contact the developer via the app’s Google Play listing or project repository.
